    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "see but it's not just \"disorientation\" tho. i've noticed it's always the same specific geometric spacing. like, it feels intentional. if companies can use color psychology to make us buy stuff, why couldn't they use these specific visual frequencies to subtly influence how we act or how compliant we are? it feels like a way to nudge people without them even knowing it's happening.",
