      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of subliminal or subtle visual messaging in fashion is part of how marketing works, often leveraging color and design theory. However, transitioning that to controlled, subconscious behavioral manipulation through specific geometric frequencies is a huge, unsubstantiated leap. While patterns certainly affect mood and perception, current mainstream psychology does not support the notion of precise, intentional geometric spacing in textiles controlling complex compliance or behavior in the way you describe.",
